23:31.000 --> 23:42.000
Ladies and gentlemen friends of Tennessee.

23:42.000 --> 23:49.000
Local governments are in a bad fix where development of much needed community facilities are concerned.

23:49.000 --> 24:00.000
When cities or communities or counties of Tennessee and all the other states want to borrow money to pay for such things as water and sewer systems to meet our exploding population groups.

24:00.000 --> 24:08.000
They are finding that very frequently they can't afford the high interest rate that they have to pay.

24:08.000 --> 24:17.000
Therefore I have again joined with pleasure in sponsoring a community facilities bill with Senator Bill Fulbright of Arkansas.

24:17.000 --> 24:23.000
This bill was introduced by us within the past few days in the United States Senate.

24:23.000 --> 24:27.000
An identical bill has been before the House for some weeks now.

24:27.000 --> 24:32.000
Last year the Senate passed a community facilities bill and a good one.

24:32.000 --> 24:38.000
But it got caught in the log jam at the end of the Congress and didn't pass in the House of Representatives.

24:38.000 --> 24:49.000
Senator Fulbright and others who are interested in this bill expect to push as hard as we know how to see that we get a bill passed in this session of Congress.

24:49.000 --> 25:03.000
The bill would expand the housing and home finance community facilities loan program to make it possible for small communities in our state and others to secure loans at interest rates that they can afford to pay.

25:03.000 --> 25:18.000
The Tennessee Municipal League which has worked hard for such legislation pointed out in recent hearings on the House bill that an enormous backlog of currently needed public works facilities and improvements exceeding half a billion dollars.

25:18.000 --> 25:26.000
Exist in the urban areas of Tennessee and are the direct obligations of our municipal governments.

25:26.000 --> 25:35.000
A survey conducted by the league shows that the need for sewer and water system developments alone run to about $180 million.

25:36.000 --> 25:52.000
Here's an example. A O'Neill, Tennessee, a splendid community of about 3,000 population is struggling to provide facilities needed to accommodate new industrial expansion and a new and an increased population.

25:52.000 --> 26:03.000
A $1 million improvement in its water and sewer sewage facilities has been recommended by an engineering study to overcome O'Neill's backlog of needs.

26:03.000 --> 26:10.000
O'Neill's officials find that the interest rates that they would have to pay run from 5 to 5 and 3,4%.

26:10.000 --> 26:24.000
And they ask how can this community produce the revenues for an annual debt amortization charge of $55,000 for interest and more than $30,000 for retirement of principal.

26:24.000 --> 26:32.000
